# Per-College Dynamic Branding & Theming System

A production-grade, SaaS-level solution to allow each of your 100+ colleges to have their own custom branding colors across all 13+ portals and 200+ screens, while keeping a sensible default and never breaking existing functionality.

## Problem Statement

Currently, branding colors like `#43C17A` (primary green), `#1E7745` (dark green), `#272372` (secondary purple) are **hardcoded** directly into Tailwind class names across 600+ file occurrences. This means:
- Every college sees the exact same green/purple theme
- Changing a college's brand requires editing 600+ lines of code
- It's impossible to serve different themes to different tenants at runtime

## Architecture Overview

```mermaid
graph TD
    A["Supabase DB: college_branding table"] -->|API Fetch on Login| B["BrandingProvider (React Context)"]
    B -->|Sets CSS Variables on :root| C["document.documentElement.style"]
    C -->|Tailwind v4 @theme references CSS vars| D["All 200+ Screens Auto-Themed"]
    E["Super Admin Panel"] -->|CRUD branding per college| A
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Core Principle**: We replace hardcoded hex colors with CSS custom properties (variables). Tailwind v4's `@theme inline` already maps CSS vars to utility classes. We extend this pattern so that the variables can be overridden at runtime per-college.

