## Phase 2: CSS Variable Token System

### 2.1 Update `globals.css` — Define Branding Tokens

We add a new set of CSS custom properties specifically for branding. These act as the **single source of truth** that all components reference.

#### [MODIFY] [globals.css](file:///d:/collpoll_client/app/globals.css)

```css
/* ============================================================
   BRANDING TOKENS (Dynamic Per-College)
   These CSS variables are the ONLY place branding colors live.
   They are overridden at runtime by the BrandingProvider.
   ============================================================ */
:root {
  --brand-primary: #43C17A;
  --brand-primary-dark: #1E7745;
  --brand-primary-light: #E6F9EF;
  --brand-primary-foreground: #FFFFFF;
  --brand-secondary: #272372;
  --brand-secondary-foreground: #FFFFFF;
  --brand-accent: #43C17A;

  /* Navbar-specific */
  --brand-navbar-bg: #43C17A;
  --brand-navbar-active-bg: #F4F4F4;
  --brand-navbar-active-text: #43C17A;
  --brand-navbar-hover-bg: rgba(80, 214, 137, 0.3);

  /* Scrollbar */
  --brand-scrollbar-thumb: #43C17A;
}
```

### 2.2 Update `@theme inline` to Reference Brand Tokens

The existing `@theme inline` block in `globals.css` already defines `--color-primary`. We update it to reference the branding tokens:

```css
@theme inline {
  --font-sans: "Jost", sans-serif;
  --color-primary: var(--brand-primary);
  --color-primary-foreground: var(--brand-primary-foreground);
  --color-secondary: var(--brand-secondary);
  --color-secondary-foreground: var(--brand-secondary-foreground);
  --color-ring: var(--brand-accent);
  /* ... rest stays the same */
}
```

### 2.3 Update Scrollbar & Selection to Use Variables

```css
.custom-scrollbar::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb {
  background: var(--brand-scrollbar-thumb);
}
.custom-scrollbar {
  scrollbar-color: var(--brand-scrollbar-thumb) #f4f4f4 !important;
}
::selection {
  background-color: color-mix(in srgb, var(--brand-primary) 30%, transparent);
}
```

